Friends and others: <br><br>
I came across a very interesting short story in The Atlantic Monthly Magazine June 1997, today, while sitting in a Toyota Dealer's waiting room, waiting for my car. I don't normally read this magazine, and as I skimmed through it, I saw, and immediately read a short story called: &quot;The Fragging&quot; by Larry Heinemann.  It really got me thinking, about fragging, if this story was valid, and to the very nature of authority itself.  <br><br>
I offer you the URL for the story:    <br><br>
http://www.TheAtlantic.com/atlantic/issues/97jun/heineman.htm<br><br>
I urge you to read this quite well written story. No information on the author was available, or I missed it.<br><br>
What do you think of it? Did things like this happen, if so how common or uncommon?  I think that you, the grunts in the bush, need to log in your thoughts on this.  This is another dirty little secret from that dirty little war, like drug use, or abuse, that needs to be explored.<br><br>
Please, add your thoughts here, for me, for you, for all of us. If you can, read the story.  It must be at bookstores, but it is downloadable and readible at the URL listed above.<br><br>
